README nvidia

POST-INSTALL

	Add your user to the "video" group to be able to use the nvidia
	devices required for 3D to function properly:

		usermod -aG video <USER>

INITRAMFS

	If you want to ensure nvidia drivers are loaded at the earliest
	possible occasion, or are noticing startup issues (such as the nvidia
	kernel module being loaded after the display manager) you can add
	nvidia, nvidia_modeset, nvidia_uvm and nvidia_drm to the initramfs.

	In case of mkinitramfs, create the hook
	/etc/mkinitramfs/hooks/nvidia/nvidia with the following content:

		#!/bin/sh
		# /etc/mkinitramfs/hooks/nvidia/nvidia:
		#     copy nvidia modules to initramfs image
		copy_kmod nvidia
		copy_kmod nvidia_uvm
		copy_kmod nvidia_drm
		copy_kmod nvidia_modeset

	Next, add "nvidia" to your hooks variable in /etc/mkinitramfs/config:

		hooks="... nvidia"

	And update initramfs image:

		kernver=$(uname -r)
		mkinitramfs -o /boot/initramfs-$kernver.img -k $kernver -f

End of file.
